<TITLE> Sonamasjid land port closed for business for 10 days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainababganj, Sep 18 (bdnews24.com)All import and export work at Sonamasjid land port will remain suspended for 10 days from Sep 20-29 for Eid-ul-Fitr and Durga Puja festivals. But the port's customs department will reopen after Eid vacation. Government holiday will end on Tuesday if Eid falls on Monday, while it will be extended up to Wednesday if Eid is observed on Tuesday, depending on the visibility of the moon. Exporters and importers along with clearing and forwarding agents from both Bangladesh and India made the decision. Sonamasjid Land Port Clearing and Forwarding Association secretary Ruhul Amin told bdnews24.com Sonamasjid port and Mohadipur land port of India would suspend import and export operations for five days from Sunday for Eid-ul-Fitr and another four days for Durga Puja. The port would cease functioning for 10 days including weekly holiday-Friday. Assistant commissioner of customs department of Sonamasjid land port, Mahbubul Alam, said the customs department would reopen as per government decision. bdnews24
